{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777264924406,"sessionID":"ses_232c2ab9dffeLQTYs7P8HYXiDQ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"background_output","callID":"call_NXRXAK6yfh1bTOtbgFNKTmGc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"block":false,"full_session":false,"include_thinking":false,"include_tool_results":false,"message_limit":10,"since_message_id":"","task_id":"bg_af40e244","thinking_max_chars":2000,"timeout":60000},"output":"Task Result\n\nTask ID: bg_af40e244\nDescription: Inspect project skeleton\nDuration: 1m 1s\nSession ID: ses_232c26813ffeGKITbTppzTudWx\n\n---\n\nI have inspected the requested project and task directories. Below is the report on the current state and recommendations for decomposition.\n\n### 1. Existing Files and Project Structure\nThe project `github-hot-repos-report` is in the **planning** phase and contains the following directory skeleton:\n- `.agent-project/`: Project metadata and state.\n- `README.md`: High-level project objectives, boundaries (no tokens, no secrets), and target directory structure.\n- `reports/`: Intended for per-period hot repository reports.\n- `scripts/`: Intended for data collection and processing tools.\n- `state/`: For lightweight status tracking.\n\nThe task directory `task_20260427_124029_cdeffd` contains:\n- `task.md`: Detailed instructions for the Engineering Leader (the current role).\n- `meta.json`, `claims.jsonl`, `submissions.jsonl`: Task Hall orchestration files.\n\n### 2. Prior Plans, Reports, and Handoffs\n- **Prior Plan**: The `README.md` and the `task.md` serve as the initial plan. The `task.md` explicitly defines the \"Total Goal\" (establishing the first version of the project skeleton and process).\n- **Handoffs**: I retrieved the `project-manager current` and `agent-guide` status. The project is \"ready\" for an `engineering-leader` to take over and delegate to a `builder`. \n- **Current State**: No implementation (scripts or reports) exists yet. The project is effectively a \"clean slate\" within the